♪ Come along with me ♪

28:37.880 --> 28:39.750
♪ Feelin' wild and free ♪

28:39.750 --> 28:41.920
♪ Everybody ♪

28:50.000 --> 28:51.420
I'm sorry
I ruined your party.

28:51.420 --> 28:52.960
Are you kidding?
Everyone in town's

28:52.960 --> 28:54.500
gonna be talking
about that tomorrow.

28:54.500 --> 28:58.500
Oh, and besides, I got you
like a dozen phone numbers.

28:58.500 --> 29:01.330
Oh.
Uh, thanks.

29:01.330 --> 29:03.290
That's, um...

29:03.290 --> 29:05.790
Oh, hey,
these are cute kids.

29:05.790 --> 29:07.000
Sorry I didn't get a chance
to meet 'em.

29:07.000 --> 29:09.170
Oh, yeah.
They're in London right now.

29:09.170 --> 29:11.880
I haven't spoken to them
in months.
That's sad.

29:11.880 --> 29:14.000
I try to talk to my son
at least once a week.

29:14.000 --> 29:16.830
Although, it's been
a little longer than
that this time around.

29:18.420 --> 29:21.920
Sacrifices we make
for our careers, huh?

29:21.920 --> 29:24.000
God, sometimes I wonder
if it's worth it.

29:24.000 --> 29:27.830
You know, these movies I make,
make a fortune,

29:27.830 --> 29:30.710
but I haven't made a film
anyone's cared about in years.

29:30.710 --> 29:31.920
Oh, you're kidding,
right?

29:31.920 --> 29:34.210
I mean, people love
your movies.

29:34.210 --> 29:36.040
The escape it brings them?
Uh...

29:36.040 --> 29:38.420
Life is hard.
Your movies are fun.

29:38.420 --> 29:40.000
But they're not real.

29:40.000 --> 29:42.040
Not like today was real.

29:42.040 --> 29:44.330
Look, let me
tell you something.

29:44.330 --> 29:47.540
Some of my fondest memories
of my son growing up

29:47.540 --> 29:49.420
are tied to your movies.

29:49.420 --> 29:52.580
Uh, he was 10
when we saw the first,

29:52.580 --> 29:55.250
and we were re-creating scenes
in the backyard.

29:55.250 --> 29:57.710
I mean, it was a blast.

29:57.710 --> 30:00.670
Every summer after that, we'd go
to an opening weekend and --

30:00.670 --> 30:02.040
Actually,
we just talked about

30:02.040 --> 30:03.330
how we're gonna schedule
the next one

30:03.330 --> 30:04.790
with him being away
at college.

30:07.620 --> 30:09.040
Thank you.

30:09.040 --> 30:10.670
Yeah. Welcome.

30:10.670 --> 30:13.500
And, um, uh,
thanks for the invite.

30:13.500 --> 30:16.330
J-John...

30:16.330 --> 30:18.670
What's gonna happen
to the kid from today?

30:18.670 --> 30:20.880
After he gets out
of hospital,

30:20.880 --> 30:22.040
will he get the care
he needs?

30:23.380 --> 30:25.330
Honestly, no.

30:25.330 --> 30:26.710
They just don't have
the means.

30:26.710 --> 30:30.420
Um, sadly, the system
is designed to deal with crisis,

30:30.420 --> 30:32.210
not prevent it.

30:33.580 --> 30:36.170
Um...thanks.

30:36.170 --> 30:42.670
♪♪

30:42.670 --> 30:45.380
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

30:45.380 --> 30:46.750
Sir, last night --

30:46.750 --> 30:48.210
Didn't happen.

30:48.210 --> 30:50.040
That clear?

30:50.040 --> 30:51.830
Hey,

30:51.830 --> 30:54.170
I got some bad news.

30:54.170 --> 30:55.250
Can't be worse
than yesterday.

30:55.250 --> 30:57.380
See, I'm afraid it can.

30:57.380 --> 30:59.210
Detectives executed
a search warrant

30:59.210 --> 31:01.380
on your wife's apartment
this morning.

31:01.380 --> 31:05.000
They found a kilo
hidden in the heating unit.

31:05.000 --> 31:07.790
She's with her lawyer now.

31:07.790 --> 31:09.330
I'm sorry, Tim.

31:09.330 --> 31:13.500
[ Indistinct conversations,
telephones ringing ]

31:17.580 --> 31:20.620
You did the right thing.

31:20.620 --> 31:23.460
Not for Isabel.

31:25.460 --> 31:28.830
So, the kilo bumps you up
to a major trafficker,

31:28.830 --> 31:33.120
which means you're facing
10 to 20 now.

31:33.120 --> 31:34.960
Now, you were
a decorated officer

31:34.960 --> 31:37.960
who got addicted on the job.

31:37.960 --> 31:39.960
We could try to use that.

31:39.960 --> 31:42.580
I went down the rabbit hole
after I got hooked.

31:42.580 --> 31:45.580
They could've investigated me
for half a dozen things.

31:45.580 --> 31:49.830
Instead, they brushed it under
the rug and fired me quietly.

31:49.830 --> 31:52.120
I'm nothing
but dirty laundry to them.

31:52.120 --> 31:54.290
Now they've got a clean shot,

31:54.290 --> 31:55.500
they're gonna take it.

31:59.380 --> 32:02.750
Major Crimes took a run at your
intel on Lawrence Abuto.

32:02.750 --> 32:06.170
They couldn't do anything with
your informant's information.

32:06.170 --> 32:08.170
Are they sure? 'Cause we had
that guy wrapped up with a bow.

32:08.170 --> 32:10.500
He was lying to you,
Officer Lopez.

32:10.500 --> 32:13.210
Frankly, I'm surprised
you couldn't tell.

32:13.210 --> 32:14.210
Ma'am, I believed him,
as well.

32:14.210 --> 32:16.620
Officer West, you're a rookie.

32:16.620 --> 32:18.460
Lopez, you're a veteran.

32:18.460 --> 32:20.420
You're usually a lot more
careful than this.

32:20.420 --> 32:22.330
I'm really disappointed in you.

32:22.330 --> 32:24.500
Yes, ma'am.

32:30.960 --> 32:33.120
I heard you were the life
of the party last night.
Did Rupert tell you that?

32:33.120 --> 32:35.670
No, I heard it from
the midnight shift.
So, was it any fun?
No.

32:35.670 --> 32:38.330
Uh, i-it was interesting.

32:38.330 --> 32:41.170
I find the whole Hollywood
thing depressing.

32:41.170 --> 32:44.830
All that energy spent on stuff
that just doesn't matter.

32:44.830 --> 32:47.880
Oh, hey,
here's your BFF now.

32:47.880 --> 32:50.250
Oh. You can get that.

32:50.250 --> 32:52.750
Hey. Rupert.
Tell m--
Help!

32:52.750 --> 32:54.750
They're trying to kill me.

32:54.750 --> 32:56.250
You've got to come.

32:56.250 --> 32:57.710
-My office.
-Rupert!

32:57.710 --> 32:59.920
His office
is on the studio lot.

32:59.920 --> 33:03.620
Dispatch, we have a possible 207
at Beverly Oaks Studios.

33:03.620 --> 33:05.210
Rupert:
John, are you still there?

33:05.210 --> 33:06.710
-I think I lost them.

33:06.710 --> 33:08.170
Rupert, are you okay?
We're on our way.

33:08.170 --> 33:10.080
I've locked myself
in the prop room.

33:10.080 --> 33:11.670
What's going on?

33:11.670 --> 33:13.330
I kept thinking about
what happened yesterday,

33:13.330 --> 33:15.210
so I reached out
to Tyson's brother.

33:15.210 --> 33:16.620
Look, a-at first,
everything was fine,

33:16.620 --> 33:18.830
but then when I offered him
money to pay for a facility,

33:18.830 --> 33:20.460
he got really angry.

33:20.460 --> 33:22.380
He started to hit me,
and then his friends --

33:22.380 --> 33:25.000
Man:
Down here!
Oh, God...

33:25.000 --> 33:27.250
His friends...
Man #2: Which way?!
Come on!

33:27.250 --> 33:29.000
...wanted me to open the safe
in my office,

33:29.000 --> 33:30.540
but I managed to get away.

33:30.540 --> 33:31.620
Rajon:
Where'd he go?

33:31.620 --> 33:32.880
Oh, God.

33:32.880 --> 33:34.080
John, help. Help!

33:36.040 --> 33:37.500
-No, no, no, no, no!
-Please. Guys, please. Please.

33:37.500 --> 33:39.460
We gotta forget about him.
Yo, let's get out of here!

33:39.460 --> 33:40.790
No, not until we get
all that money

33:40.790 --> 33:41.960
from that safe
in his office.

33:41.960 --> 33:45.040
-I don't want his money.
Well, we do.

33:45.040 --> 33:46.790
-Back to the offi--

33:46.790 --> 33:48.500
I've lost him.

33:48.500 --> 33:57.170
♪♪

33:59.210 --> 34:00.580
His office
is in that building.

34:04.290 --> 34:08.960
♪♪

34:08.960 --> 34:10.670
-Stop! Police!
-Don't move!

34:17.380 --> 34:18.670
Aah!

34:21.290 --> 34:23.330
-Go get him.
-On it.

34:24.790 --> 34:27.210
Cuff him and call it in!

34:27.210 --> 34:29.330
Hands behind your back.

34:31.960 --> 34:33.500
Man: So, you want to get
your cameras ready

34:33.500 --> 34:35.420
'cause up here to my left

34:35.420 --> 34:37.960
is a sign you'll
probably recognize...

34:40.920 --> 34:50.920
♪♪

34:50.920 --> 34:54.830
♪♪

35:18.960 --> 35:20.460
Nolan: Malcolm, stop!

35:20.460 --> 35:22.080
Your mother's suffered enough.

35:22.080 --> 35:24.790
You're only making it worse.

35:24.790 --> 35:27.000
Malcolm: You gonna be
my savior now, too

35:27.000 --> 35:30.120
Like Mr. Hollywood here?
Offering me money to make
himself feel like a hero --

35:30.120 --> 35:31.790
To put your brother
in a facility.

35:31.790 --> 35:33.750
Yeah, and what happens
when that runs out, huh?

35:33.750 --> 35:35.880
How we supposed to pay for your
fancy

35:35.880 --> 35:37.670
You gonna give us money for next
year and the year after that?

35:37.670 --> 35:40.000
-I told you, we'll work it out.

35:40.000 --> 35:42.000
Like it's that simple, huh?

35:42.000 --> 35:43.960
Like my brother's just
gonna be fixed now that
you're here to save the day.

35:43.960 --> 35:45.080
Malcolm,
he doesn't understand.

35:45.080 --> 35:48.580
-No. God, no.

35:48.580 --> 35:49.750
I've never been
in your shoes.

35:49.750 --> 35:52.040
I-I can't imagine

35:52.040 --> 35:53.920
what it's been like
for you and your mom

35:53.920 --> 35:55.250
to have to care
for your brother,

35:55.250 --> 35:56.290
to make sure he doesn't
hurt himself,

35:56.290 --> 35:57.790
that he can never be alone.

35:57.790 --> 35:59.250
Then to have this

35:59.250 --> 36:01.540
poster child for entitlement
call you up like that?

36:01.540 --> 36:02.920
-Hey.
-Shh!

36:02.920 --> 36:04.670
It's gotta be
infuriating.

36:07.250 --> 36:08.500
But this...

36:11.120 --> 36:14.120
...Malcolm, this --
this helps no one.

36:14.120 --> 36:15.620
This only hurts
your brother,

36:15.620 --> 36:20.210
and I know you don't
want to do that.

36:20.210 --> 36:22.330
So, come on.
Let's...put the gun down

36:22.330 --> 36:23.540
and let's just end this,
okay?

36:28.040 --> 36:29.960
I got it! I got it!

36:29.960 --> 36:30.880
-Drop the weapon!
-No!

36:32.500 --> 36:34.790
-Oh!
-No! Come here.

36:34.790 --> 36:36.500
Ohh...

36:42.920 --> 36:44.420
-I got shot.
-Yeah.

36:44.420 --> 36:46.580
It really hurts.

36:46.580 --> 36:47.790
Don't worry, they're gonna take
good care of you.

36:47.790 --> 36:49.040
ER's just
five minutes away.

36:49.040 --> 36:50.290
Will you visit me
in the hospital?

36:50.290 --> 36:51.670
Of course, yes.

36:51.670 --> 36:53.880
Hey, please, tell Malcolm
I'm sorry.

36:53.880 --> 36:55.170
I-I-I had no idea.

36:58.750 --> 37:00.620
-Paramedics seem to think so.

37:00.620 --> 37:02.500
Good, then I don't have to wait
to yell at you

37:02.500 --> 37:04.380
about getting your VIP shot.

37:04.380 --> 37:05.790
Well, technically,
the ride along was yesterday,

37:05.790 --> 37:07.250
so...

37:07.250 --> 37:09.540
Never mind.

37:09.540 --> 37:11.500
We're transferring your wife
to county.

37:11.500 --> 37:13.420
Arraignment will be tomorrow.

37:20.210 --> 37:22.290
I'm sorry.

37:22.290 --> 37:24.920
I needed you,
and you weren't there.

37:24.920 --> 37:26.250
It wouldn't have
fixed things.

37:26.250 --> 37:28.580
You don't know that!

37:28.580 --> 37:31.500
Now you never will.
We're done here.

37:31.500 --> 37:34.620
♪♪

37:36.170 --> 37:39.460
♪♪

37:39.460 --> 37:41.170
Hey.
Been looking for you.

37:43.670 --> 37:45.210
What's wrong?

37:45.210 --> 37:47.790
The Jason is in ICU.

37:47.790 --> 37:50.620
What, you mean the guy
who likes to shock himself?

37:50.620 --> 37:54.500
The guy he flipped on
found out about it.

37:54.500 --> 37:57.380
Beat him half to death
with a pipe.

37:57.380 --> 38:00.000
[ Door buzzes, opens
in distance ]

38:00.000 --> 38:01.880
Th-That's not on us.

38:01.880 --> 38:04.420
No, it's on me.

38:04.420 --> 38:07.170
If I hadn't been so gung ho
on getting The Tap,

38:07.170 --> 38:08.330
he'd be in the house
of detention,

38:08.330 --> 38:12.170
looking at a few months
of jail.

38:12.170 --> 38:14.750
Now he might not be able
to walk again.

38:14.750 --> 38:16.500
There's no way you could've
known about that.

38:16.500 --> 38:19.620
Maybe.

38:19.620 --> 38:22.290
But I didn't even think about
it, and I should have.

38:24.710 --> 38:29.670
You, um, think this will
move you down the list?

38:29.670 --> 38:31.170
Are you kidding?
I'm off the list.

38:33.290 --> 38:35.210
Gonna have to earn my way
back onto it.

38:38.880 --> 38:43.210
Anything I can do
to help...I will.

38:43.210 --> 38:46.000
You had my back
when I needed it.

38:51.040 --> 38:53.920
Oh, right.
I almost forgot.

38:53.920 --> 38:55.380
Did you hear
about Tim's wife?

39:12.880 --> 39:14.830
What are you doing?

39:14.830 --> 39:16.080
Hanging out with you.

39:18.920 --> 39:22.290
Look, I appreciate
the thought, but...

39:22.290 --> 39:24.080
I'd rather be alone.
Too bad.

39:24.080 --> 39:25.330
I'm not gonna talk
about it.

39:25.330 --> 39:26.960
You don't have to.

39:26.960 --> 39:28.750
But we're gonna be here
if you change your mind.

39:35.710 --> 39:37.620
So what do we do now?

39:37.620 --> 39:38.540
Together: Drink.

39:39.830 --> 39:47.040
♪♪

39:47.040 --> 39:48.420
-Hey.
-Hey.

39:48.420 --> 39:50.250
-Well, it is now.

39:50.250 --> 39:53.420
Hey, I saw the news
about Rupert.

39:53.420 --> 39:55.080
You okay?
Yeah.

39:55.080 --> 39:58.120
Days like today
can be hard emotionally.

39:58.120 --> 39:59.790
I'll bet.

39:59.790 --> 40:02.830
Well, I have a plus-one
to a gallery opening.

40:02.830 --> 40:06.000
You can come if you want
and take your mind off it.

40:06.000 --> 40:07.920
Yeah, you know what?
I'm -- I'm beat.

40:07.920 --> 40:09.210
You sure? I mean...

40:09.210 --> 40:11.330
I-I-I can stay home
if you don't want to be alone.

40:11.330 --> 40:12.210
I won't be.

40:14.500 --> 40:15.710
Okay.

40:17.880 --> 40:19.040
You have a good night.

40:19.040 --> 40:20.710
I will.

40:20.710 --> 40:25.500
♪ The hardest thing to do ♪

40:28.000 --> 40:30.580
♪ But I'll be here for you ♪

40:32.790 --> 40:38.330
♪ When the world's too heavy
and you can't move ♪

40:38.330 --> 40:40.790
♪ Oh, I'll be here ♪

40:42.250 --> 40:44.080
-Hey, buddy.

40:44.080 --> 40:45.330
Oh, it's good
to see your face.

40:45.330 --> 40:47.710
I'm sorry I haven't called
in a few days.

40:47.710 --> 40:50.290
I've just been crazy
with work.

40:50.290 --> 40:52.290
No worries.
I'm slammed myself.

40:52.290 --> 40:54.620
-Yeah, great.

40:54.620 --> 40:57.540
Uh, we're reading "Catch-22,"
which I love.

40:57.540 --> 41:00.170
And, uh, my roommate moved in
with his girlfriend,

41:00.170 --> 41:02.460
so got the dorm all to myself.

41:02.460 --> 41:03.920
Sweet.

41:03.920 --> 41:05.830
Um, tell me what
you think of this.

41:05.830 --> 41:07.210
Uh...

41:07.210 --> 41:09.290
What if I was to book
you a flight

41:09.290 --> 41:10.750
and you come to L.A.,
just visit a few days?

41:10.750 --> 41:12.460
I've got midterms next week,

41:12.460 --> 41:14.500
but after that, I am --
I am all in.

41:14.500 --> 41:16.540
Awesome. Okay, uh,
text me the dates,

41:16.540 --> 41:19.250
and I'll book the flights.
Meantime...

41:19.250 --> 41:22.420
you will never guess
who I met.

41:22.420 --> 41:24.000
Rupert Payne.

41:24.000 --> 41:25.670
Wait.

41:25.670 --> 41:27.960
D-Did I see
that he just got shot?
Yeah.

41:27.960 --> 41:29.830
-Yeah, crazy story.

41:29.830 --> 41:31.290
-Oh, tell me. Tell me.
-Okay, um,

41:31.290 --> 41:32.710
you remember
"Trading Fire Two,"

41:32.710 --> 41:34.420
when the hostage
took the gun and we said,

41:34.420 --> 41:36.080
"Totally unbelievable.
It would never happen"?
Yeah.

41:36.080 --> 41:38.210
Okay, earlier in the day,
we respond to a call.

41:38.210 --> 41:39.790
Cut to a family
in a front yard,

41:39.790 --> 41:41.920
frying pan,
burning pancakes...

41:46.540 --> 41:56.500
♪♪

41:56.500 --> 42:06.540
♪♪

42:06.540 --> 42:16.540
♪♪

42:16.540 --> 42:22.080
♪♪
